# ── APIClient fork: scratch + regenerable artifacts ──────────────────
# The forced-execution work generates many throwaway fixtures, capture
# dumps, and rebuildable wasm. None belong in history. The real
# green-gate fixtures are force-added (git add -f) so they survive the
# `_*` blanket below — see the "Fork version-control system" section in
# APIClient/CLAUDE.md.
#
# Regenerable build outputs (node engine/build.mjs ...):
qjs_wasm.*
qjs_mod.*
qjs_worker.*
pre.gen.js
# Scratch logs / temp / bytecode / backups:
*.tmp
*.out
*.err
*.bc
*.bak*
*.scripts.json
*.pre.js
t.tr
diag.txt
# Scratch fixtures, probes, and multi-MB site captures (regenerable via
# `harness dumpscripts`). Blanket — the named gate fixtures are tracked
# via `git add -f`, which overrides this.
_*
# Stray one-offs:
.t.gh
vue.js
jq.js
jq.out
